asset.hookText:
http://odyssey.tagheuer.com - Throughout the summer, the TAG Heuer Tesla Roadster was driven accross the US and stopped in cities nationwide. New York was the last stop in the US.

After a short visit of Manhattan, the TAG Heuer Tesla roadster was driven to the Hamptons, in Amagansett, where TAG Heuer hosted and invitation-only event, held at a private estate. 

Golden Globe, Emmy and Tony award-winning actress Mary Louise Parker, Musician Charlie Mars, Grammy nominated R+B singer Maxwell, Ed Westwick, star of the hit TV show "Gossip Girls", Hilary Rhoda, supermodel, and Cornelia Guest, New York social influencer and philanthropist, were among the elite guests who came to celebrate our anniversary.
